      "content": "I hear the profound exhaustion in your words, and it makes sense that when every attempt to move forward just leads back to the same starting point, the \"one more try\" mentality feels like a cruel joke. It is incredibly draining to constantly pretend that the outcome will be different when the pattern is so rigid and unyielding, like a wheel spinning in place while the world moves on without you.\n\nSometimes, when the internal struggle becomes this heavy, the only thing that feels possible is to stop fighting the wheel entirely and let the spinning happen, even if it feels pointless. You don't have to solve the loop right this second, especially when the pressure to fix it is what's keeping you stuck in the very cycle you're trying to escape.\n\nIt sounds like you are carrying a weight that feels impossible to lift, but even the heaviest load can be shared if you find someone who can sit with you in the dark without trying to force the light out. Would you be willing to talk about what specifically feels like the \"thing inside it\" that needs to stop? Sometimes identifying the core pressure point can help, even if just for a moment, to see if the loop might finally break.",
